result.execSummary:
The defendant Jack Dean Conley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Receiving or Concealing Stolen Property (<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.34(1)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jack Dean Conley in court with attorney Joseph James Dorlack.  Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Amended information filed. Atty Dorlack waives formal reading. Defendant enters a guilty plea to count #1 and #2 of the Amended Information. Court performs plea colloquy and finds defendant guilty of count #1 and #2 of the Amended Information. State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Dorlack makes statements regarding sentencing. Atty Dorlack requests expungement. Defendant makes Statements. The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

___ 120 DAYS HUBER (CREDIT - 3 days)	***CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT#2***

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR	***CONCURRENT TO COUNT #2***

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
_____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
_____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling , 
_____Completion of High School Diploma or Equivilency
_____Maintain and comply with any child support orders
_____No use of the victims identifying or financial information
_____Defendant to report to the Waukesha County Sheriff Department within (3) business days to provide DNA sample.

COSTS:  $243.00 + $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME: 30 days-Non-working hours with standard release conditions, STAYED for use of agent with court permission.

COUNT#2:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

___ 120 DAYS HUBER 	***CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT#1***

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR	***CONCURRENT TO COUNT #1***

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
_____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
_____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling , 
_____Completion of High School Diploma or Equivilency
_____Maintain and comply with any child support orders
_____No use of the victims identifying or financial information
_____Defendant to report to the Waukesha County Sheriff Department within (3) business days to provide DNA sample.

COSTS:  $243.00  (to be paid as a condition of probation)

Expungement is denied.
